						<summary>

						<p>The record is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 963 (= A.D. 1041-42),</hi> further details having been lost. It refers itself to the reign of the Chālukya king <hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalla</hi> and registers gifts of land to a temple (name lost) by the <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Hosavaḍaṅgile.</hi> It also records a gift to the goddess Sarasvatīdēvī.</p>						

						</summary>
